# Cursor Rules — stockanalysis

## Project
Data ingestion ETL. Fetches NASDAQ 100 + NSE 500 + Forex prices and fundamentals → SQL Server.

## Stack
- Python 3.11+, yfinance, pandas, pyodbc, alpha_vantage
- SQL Server (localhost\MSSQLSERVER01, stockdata_db, Windows Auth)

## Architecture
- fetch_nasdaq_data.py → nasdaq_100_hist_data (VARCHAR prices!)
- fetch_nse_data.py → nse_500_hist_data (VARCHAR prices!)
- fetch_forex_data.py → forex_hist_data (DECIMAL prices)
- fetch_fundamentals.py → *_fundamentals tables
- sql_loader.py → Generic bulk loader
- manage_tickers.py → Ticker master list management

## Critical Notes
- Equity prices stored as VARCHAR — ALL downstream MUST CAST to FLOAT
- Forex prices stored as DECIMAL — no casting needed
- Alpha Vantage: 5 calls/min free tier rate limit
- Upsert on ticker + trading_date prevents duplicates

## Unused (ignore)
- dags/ — Legacy Airflow DAGs
- Snowflake/DataHub references — dead code

## Ecosystem
Foundation layer for 7-repo platform. Every other repo depends on data loaded here. If ingestion fails, entire pipeline breaks.
- sqlserver_mcp — .NET 8 MCP Server (Microsoft MssqlMcp): 7 tools (ListTables, DescribeTable, ReadData, CreateTable, DropTable, InsertData, UpdateData) via stdio. Use to explore DB schemas/data during development.

